Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @Baby Potatoes{500%grams} into 2cm chunks.

Pop onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic{1%unit}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, mix the @Cajun Spice Mix{2%sachet}, garlic, @Honey{1%sachet} and @oil{1%tbsp} (double for 4p).

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Season with salt and pepper.

Add the @Irish Chicken Breast{320%grams} and turn to coat in the marinade.

> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don't worry, this is normal due to packaging we use to keep it fresh.

Meanwhile, trim the @Carrot{1%unit}(trimmed and sliced) and @Parsnip{1%unit}(trimmed and sliced) then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Slice widthways into pieces about ½ cm thick.

Pop onto a (separate) lined baking tray.

Toss with salt, pepper and a drizzle of oil.

Arrange the marinated chicken next to the veg on the tray.

Roast together on the middle shelf of the oven until golden and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, trim the tip of the @Broccoli{1%unit}. Cut head into small florets and stem into 2cm pieces.

When the chicken and veg have been cooking for ~{10%minutes}, remove from the oven and pop the broccoli onto the tray next to them.

Season with oil, salt and pepper.

Cook for the remaining time, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Zest half the @Lemon{½%unit}(zested and cut into wedges) (double for 4p) then cut into thick wedges.

In a small bowl mix a drizzle of @oil{to taste}, the lemon zest, a squeeze of lemon juice and @Mayo{2%sachet}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Mix well to combine.

When everything is ready, slice the chicken widthways.

Plate up the sliced chicken with roast potatoes and veg alongside.

Finish with a drizzle of the lemony mayo.